prospects.name: 2 x 2K Increasing
prospects.description:
If you drill into the pacing strategies of any endurance competitor, you quickly learn that the negative split is the fastest way to complete a course. A negative split is where your pace is higher during the second half of the course; we’ll work on that pacing strategy today.

​

For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warm-Up**

10 minutes @ RPE 2-4 -- 120-145% of RTP -- HR 70-87% (Z2)

​

**Activation 1: Drills of choice: butt kicks, high knees, etc.**

Number of Sets: 2

Rest Between Sets: 30 sec

Interval Distance: 25m

**Activation 2: 150-200m Strides**

Number of Sets: 2-3

Rest Between Sets: 30 sec

Interval Effort: 110-100% RTP (Z4a)

​

**Main Effort**

Number of Sets: 2

Rest Between Sets: 5 minutes

Interval Distance Per set: 2K

Interval Effort: Begin @ RPE 5-6 --120-110% of RTP --HR 87-95% (Z3)

Steadily increase to RPE 7.5-8.5 by final 400m -- 100-92% of RTP--HR 100-105% (Z4b)

Note: Repeat the same pace on the second set, but strive to finish faster for the final 400m.

​

**Cool Down**

5-10 minutes @ RPE 2 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1)

For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

10 minutes @ RPE 2-4 -- 145-120% of RTP -- HR 70-87%

​

**Activation 1: Drills of choice: butt kicks, high knees**

Number of Sets: 2 each

Rest Between Sets: 30 sec

Interval Distance: 50m each

**Activation 2**

Number of Sets: 2

Rest Between Sets: 30 sec

Interval Distance: 100m

Interval Effort: Gradual build @ RPE 3-8 --145-92% of RTP --HR 70-105%

​

**Main Effort**

Number of Sets: 2

Rest Between Sets: 5 minutes

Interval Distance Per set: 5k

Interval Effort:RPE 5-6 --120-110% of RTP --HR 87-95%

​

**Extra Volume**

NA

**Cool Down**

prospects.name: 2 x 6K Kicking
prospects.description:
We know that triathlons are more focused on steadily paced runs, but if you’re ever going to get faster then you need to do some speed work! Find a flat track or course with regular distance markers and prepare yourself for some explosive speed work.

​

For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warm Up**

10 minutes @ RPE 1-2 -- 145-120% of RTP -- HR <70-87% (Z1)

​

**Activation 1**

Number of Sets: 3

Rest Between Sets: 30s

Interval Distance Per Set: 75m build

Interval Effort: RPE 4-10 --<120-85% of RTP --HR 87-105% (Z2-Z6)

Recovery: RPE <2 -->145% of RTP --HR <70% (Z1)

​

**Main Effort**

Number of Sets: 2

Rest Between Sets: 3 minutes

Interval Distance Per set: 6K

Interval 1 Effort: 5.9k @ RPE 3-4 -- 145-120% of RTP --HR 70-87% (Z2), Final 100m @ RPE 10 --<85% of RTP --HR 105 (Z6)

Interval 2 Effort: 5.9k @ RPE 5-6 --120-110% of RTP --HR 87-95% (Z3), Final 100m @ RPE 10 --<85% of RTP --HR 105 (Z6)

Recovery: RPE 1-2 --<145% of RTP --HR <70% (Z1)

Note: Pace it so you are increasing your speed for the last 100m and not slowing at the end.

​

**Cool Down**

5-10 minutes @ RPE 2 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1)

If you drill into the pacing strategies of any endurance competitor, you quickly learn that the negative split is the fastest way to complete a course. A negative split is where your pace is higher during the second half of the course. The goal of this workout is to practice that pacing strategy today.

Number of Sets: 3

Steadily increase to RPE 7.5 over the entire distance -- 100-92% of RTP--HR 100-105% (Z4a)

\*Strive to achieve the same pace across all three efforts.

Walk or jog for 5-10 minutes to cool down (Z1)

prospects.name: 5K Pace Test
prospects.description:
For help understanding your run workout and calculating your pace zones, please see [this article](https://wahoosystm.com/RunningSessionFAQ).

Learn how to perform your [**Running Drills**](https://support.wahoofitness.com/hc/en-us/articles/4404080091922-Running-Drills) here.

​

**Warm Up**

10 minutes @ RPE 2 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1)

5 minute build from RPE 2 to RPE 4 -- 145-120% of RTP -- HR 70-87% (Z2)

​

**Activation 1: Accelerations**

Number of Sets 2

Rest Between Sets 60-90 seconds

Interval Effort: 90sec Accelerations from RPE 4 up to RPE 7 (Z2-Z4b)

Recovery: 90 seconds @ RPE 2 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1)

**Activation 2: Strides**

Number of Sets 4-6

Rest Between Sets: 1 min

Interval Distance: 80m build

Interval Effort: Gradual increase @ RPE 3-8 (Z2 building to Z4)

Recovery: 30+ seconds @ RPE <2 -->145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1)

​

**Main Effort**

5K Test If you aren’t sure what pace you can sustain keep the RPE around 7 for the first 1500m, then build from that pace or keep it steady. Take note of your 1K splits to see if you are fading or building by the end. Record your time for the full 5k and average heart rate for the last 20 minutes. To calculate your running Lactate Threshold Heart Rate (LTHR), subtract 10bpm from the average HR of your last 20 minutes and add 15sec to your average kilometer splits to determine Running Threshold Pace (RTP).

​

**Cool Down**

5-10 minutes @ RPE 2 -- 145% of RTP -- HR <70% (Z1)

​
